Description: A sealing for an unknown object: parts of two oval impressions from intaglio gems, only one legible, with the Dioskouroi flanking a head of Sarapis. Unfired pale yellow-brown mud.
Curator's comments: Terracotta IV Donated: Egypt Exploration Society. Roman, probably second century AD.
Bibliographic references: Terracotta / Catalogue of Terracottas in the British Museum (3634)
